00112   /*
00113    * !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
00114    * ! MD5_LONG has to be at least 32 bits wide. If it's wider, then !
00115    * ! MD5_LONG_LOG2 has to be defined along.                        !
00116    * !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
00117    */
00118 
00119 #if defined(OPENSSL_SYS_WIN16) || defined(__LP32__)
00120 #define MD5_LONG unsigned long
00121 #elif defined(OPENSSL_SYS_CRAY) || defined(__ILP64__)
00122 #define MD5_LONG unsigned long
00123 #define MD5_LONG_LOG2 3
00124   /*
00125    * _CRAY note. I could declare short, but I have no idea what impact
00126    * does it have on performance on none-T3E machines. I could declare
00127    * int, but at least on C90 sizeof(int) can be chosen at compile time.
00128    * So I've chosen long...
00129    *                                      <appro@fy.chalmers.se>
00130    */
00131 #else
00132 #define MD5_LONG unsigned int
00133 #endif
00134 
00135 #define MD5_CBLOCK  64
00136 #define MD5_LBLOCK  (MD5_CBLOCK/4)
00137 #define MD5_DIGEST_LENGTH 16
